
<h2>
    Borders in CSS
</h2>
<p>
    A border consists of lines on the outside of an element that help display shape and contrast. 
    They are fully customizable with CSS, including the style, width and color of the lines. 
</p>

<p class="border border-secondary p-5">
    Border Example
</p>

<h3>
    Border Styles
</h3>

@{
    string str = @"dotted - Defines a dotted border
    dashed - Defines a dashed border
    solid - Defines a solid border
    double - Defines a double border
    groove - Defines a 3D grooved border. The effect depends on the border-color value
    ridge - Defines a 3D ridged border. The effect depends on the border-color value
    inset - Defines a 3D inset border. The effect depends on the border-color value
    outset - Defines a 3D outset border. The effect depends on the border-color value
    none - Defines no border
    hidden - Defines a hidden border";
}
<table>
@foreach (string style in str.Split("\n"))
    {
        string name =@style.Split(" - ")[0];
        string desc =@style.Split(" - ")[1];
        <tr >
            <td>
                @name
            </td>
            <td>
                <span  class="text-black" style=" border: 5px @name black">@desc </span>
            </td>
        </tr>   
    }
</table>


@foreach (string style in str.Split("\n")){
    string name =@style.Split(" - ")[0];
    <div class="pt-4 text-center bg-dark m-5" style="border: @name 10px crimson;  width: 50%; height: 100px">
        <code>border: <span style="color: crimson;">@name</span> 10px red; </code>
    </div>
}

<h3>
    Border Width
</h3>
<p>
    Border Width Controls the thickness of each border. Each size can be controlled by units (px, pt, cm, em, ...), 
    or by using the predefined <code>thin</code> <code>medium</code> <code>thick</code> properties. 
</p>
<div class="pt-4 text-center  text-light bg-dark m-5" style="border: 10px solid crimson;  width: 50%; height: 100px">
        10px Thickness
</div>
<div class="pt-4 text-center  text-light bg-dark m-5" style="border: 5px solid crimson;  width: 50%; height: 100px">
        5px Thickness
</div>
<div class="pt-4 text-center bg-light m-5" style="border: 1px solid crimson;  width: 50%; height: 100px">
        1px Thickness
</div>

<div class="pt-4 text-center m-5" style="border: thin solid crimson;  width: 50%; height: 100px">
        thin
</div>
<div class="pt-4 text-center  m-5" style="border: medium solid crimson;  width: 50%; height: 100px">
        medium
</div>
<div class="pt-4 text-center m-5" style="border: thick solid crimson;  width: 50%; height: 100px">
        thick
</div>

<p>
    Each side (left, right, top, bottom) can be independently modified and combined with 
    the other side for a cool border. 
</p>
<div class="pt-4 text-center m-5" style="border-bottom: thin solid crimson; border-right: medium solid crimson; border-left: thick solid crimson;  width: 50%; height: 100px">
        border-bottom: thin solid crimson; border-right: medium solid crimson; border-left: thick solid crimson;
</div>

